Key Match Events: Georgian striker Georges Mikautadze scored the opening goal with a penalty after a controversial VAR check for handball from Robin Hranac.
Patrik Schick equalized for the Czech Republic with a corner kick goal, helping them come from behind.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match ended in a 1-1 draw, leaving both teams with one point each in Euro 2024 Group F.
Portugal and Turkey, who play later, are on three points each.
Georgia will face Portugal in their next match, while Czech Republic will play against Turkey.
